2 unit Beyond Meat®
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
200 g Green Bell Pepper
56 g Onion, sliced
1 tbsp Cornstarch
2 tbsp Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
2 unit Green Onion
56 g Green Peas
3.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt and Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce. Rinse noodles in warm water until separated. Drain well. Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then noodles. Cook, stirring often, until crispy, 4-5 min. Remove pan from the heat and transfer noodles to a plate. Set aside.

Core, then cut peppers into 1/2-inch slices. Thinly slice green onion. Whisk together sesame oil, vegetarian oyster sauce, soy sauce, cornstarch and 1/2 cup water (dbl for 4 ppl) in a medium bowl. Set aside.

Heat the same pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then peppers and onions. Cook, stirring often, until tender-crisp, 4-5 min. Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from the heat and transfer veggies to another plate.

Heat the same pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then add the Beyond Meat. Season with salt and pepper. Break up patties into bite-sized pieces with a spatula. Cook, stirring often, until slightly crispy, 5-6 min.**

Add veggies to the pan with Beyond Meat, then add the peas and sesame sauce. Remove the pan from heat. Stir together, until slightly thickened, 2-3 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide crispy noodles between plates. Top with Beyond Meat stir-fry and sprinkle over green onions.